From 577742c8ab420e5077037ac632127c2c3dcf5456 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Dan <dm.marafino@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 1 Jul 2026 20:09:26 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Add Pantry Raider raccoon logo: icons, header mark, ghosted
 background

Wire the new brand mark (pink line-art raccoon with a fork, #F2006E) through
the app from the master logo.png:

- scripts/gen-icons.py regenerates every derivative from the master with
  Pillow (no external binaries): favicon 16/32/.ico/.svg (transparent), the
  192/512 PWA icons and apple-touch icon (white tile, safe-zone padding for
  'any maskable'), and a crisp transparent logo-mark for the header/background.
- Header + Settings brand now show the raccoon instead of the fridge glyph;
  the pink reads on both dark and light navbars.
- Default background is a faint ghosted raccoon watermark, centred and low
  opacity (0.06 dark / 0.04 light) so it never competes with page text; a
  user-set background image still replaces it. Verified across dark and light
  themes.

Master art lives at service/app/static/icons/logo.png; rerun gen-icons.py to
refresh the set if it changes.
